<br/><br/>
The distribution of the use in each animal category is further studied based on the yearly-average BD100-values of the farms in the benchmark reference population per animal category (excluding zero-use farms). These distributions are currently all skewed with a long tail of high-using farms. In Figure 8  , the evolution between 2018 and 2022 of the median BD100 from each animal category distribution is shown. In the veal calf and porcine fattener sectors, the median BD100 consistently reduced year–on–year throughout the study period, while in broilers we observed a significant decrease 2020-2021 followed by a partial rebound between 2021 and 2022. The veal calf sector displays the most significant reductions in BD100 (representing on average two weeks fewer of antimicrobial treatment per Belgian calf), however, this remains the sector with the highest antibiotic use, closely followed by weaned piglets.
